description: From Middle English thevysch, equivalent to thief +‎ -ish. Cognate with Saterland Frisian däifsk (“thievish”), Dutch diefs (“thievish”), German Low German deevsk (“thievish”), German diebisch (“thievish”).

adjectives.description: thievish (comparative more thievish, superlative most thievish)

entries.meaning: Having the manner of a thief; furtive; stealthy.
